 <caption>
  <p>Ethnomedicinal plants used by the tribal people of Rangamati for treating different diseases (source: Medicinal Plants Database of Bangladesh [
   <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR24">24</xref>â€“
   <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR26">26</xref>]). A total of 62 medicinal plant species were found out of which 26 plants treat gastrointestinal ailments (GIA), 12 plants treat respiratory system disorders (RSD). Poisonous bites (PB) and skeleton muscular system disorders (SMSD) were treated by 2 plants. Endocrinal disorders (ED), throat pain, and hemorrhoids (HEM) were healed by 3 plants. Four plants were used to cure different types of fever (Fvr). For liver problems (LP), 5 plants were used. Dermatological infections/diseases (DID) were treated using 9 different plants. Three plants were used to treat hypertension (HTN) and 2 were used to treat anemia
  </p>
